You can make this work simply using EditText, rather than using SearchView, Here is the code snippet you might want to use : 

```
Timer timer1 = null;
yourEditText.addTextChangedListener(new TextWatcher() {
            @Override
            public void beforeTextChanged(CharSequence charSequence, int i, int i1, int i2) {
                
            }

            @Override
            public void onTextChanged(CharSequence charSequence, int i, int i1, int i2) {
                if (timer1 != null) {
                    timer1.cancel();
                }
            }

            @Override
            public void afterTextChanged(Editable editable) {
                timer1 = new Timer();
                timer1.schedule(new TimerTask() {
                    @Override
                    public void run() {
                        if (getActivity() != null) {
                            getActivity().runOnUiThread(new Runnable() {
                                @Override
                                public void run() {
                                    Toast.makeText(getActivity(), &quot;Your Code Goes Here!&quot;, Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
                                }
                            });
                        }
                    }
                }, 3000 /*Delay (In Milliseconds), Whatever you want to*/);
            }
        });
```

This will cancel your calls while user types, and afterTextChange will be called after user completes his/her typing. the best Typing delay you should use is 750 ms.

Happy Coding :)

